{
  "texts": [
    "The first drop of L ϕ is correlated with a sudden increase in L phys.",
    "Similar training dynamics were already observed by Buhendwa et al. [7], who reported that the sudden learning of the interface location leads to a rapid increase in the magnitude of the gradients in the phase distribution at the interface and, in turn, an increase in the magnitude of the surface force term in the momentum equation.",
    "Furthermore, Buhendwa et al. [7] found that the sudden increase of the physics-informed losses destabilizes the optimization and can cause complete divergence.",
    "The reason is that L phys offer only limited guidance when the interface is not accurately learned and may even mislead the optimization of the neural network.",
    "This is particularly problematic for the considered water-air flow, where an erroneous prediction of the occupancy field introduces large errors in the momentum equation due to the high fluid density ratio."
  ]
}